review.reviewBody:
I have purchased the Superalloy 2P 2 years ago.  I love the tent.  Unfortunately, I had a branch fall on the rain fly and it ripped.  No problem with the quality, just bad luck.  I have been trying to get a replacement fly to purchase.  Here is the response:  &quot;Thank you for being our loyal customer.  I am sorry to inform you that this time, we do not carry spare parts for our products nor do we provide the in-house repairs, therefore, we will not be able to fulfill request.&quot;

I thought they had a lifetime warranty.  Plus, unable to support their product line?  DO NOT PURCHASE Marmot products.  Support those that actually support their products and you can get repaired and purchase replacements when things break.  Would you buy a car that the dealership cannot repair?  I will no longer be a customer and will tell all that I can to support the smaller, focused companies that appreciate their customers and their customers&apos; hard-earned money.

John
